---

I found STAT 134 to be useful for understanding the mathematics behind Gaussians and other probability distributions. It is fairly theoretical and can help you build an intuition for some topics that get covered in 189.
IMO Stat 134 isn't anywhere near a replacement for EE126. It's very slightly beyond 70 and doesn't cover most of the topics of 126.

children.subject: Ramchandran has excellent reviews and is pretty popular. Im planning on using phase I units for 126.

What do you mean by not covering all the topics for 126 though? I am more interested in the math behind the distributions than just extra applications I could maybe figure out on my own knowing the math. Does anyone know how the professor of 126 for next sem teaches?

Personally, I would not recommend anyone take stat 134. In the semester I took it, the first half of the course was an elaboration on 70-style probability. If you struggled with that and want a review, it could be okay, although it's a big commitment for (imo) a very small payoff. The second half of the course is mostly about more complicated distributions (continuous distributions/how to think about continuous random variables is taught). 126 covers a wide variety of topics that are useful across EE and CS, whereas I haven't found Stat 134 useful at all in any other classes. Again, this is all personal experience, and I'm sure other people have different experiences.

If you wish to go deeper into the statistics offerings, it could be useful to see probability taught in the statistics department, and it will save you having to email professors about prereqs in the future. But it's in no way a replacement for 126 (or CS174).

so in your opinion do you think ee 126 would be better to take along cs 189? I am only interested in taking stats 134 or ee 126 because i want to be better prepared for cs 189 and if i decide i want to go into AI.

if you aren't very comfortable with math, ee126+cs189 will be really, really brutal. IMO stat134/ee126 aren't the classes to take to prep for 189 - 189 is a lot of linear algebra, so I'd say Math 110 is the class to take if you're worried about doing well in CS189. But I don't think any of them alongside CS189 will really help - I had a friend who took Math 110 along with CS189 and he said they didn't get to the relevant concepts in time for 189.
oh i see, ill make sure to review my linear algebra beforehand. thanks a lot for your responses!
np, friend. The other student response seems to imply they had a better time with stat 134, so it might be good to get a better sense from other people, too! But that's my experience.

I mostly agree with Mike's evaluation in that it really won't help if you are taking it concurrently with 189. In my case I just happened to be able to make the connections to 189 material after Stat 134, but I don't think it's worth going out of your way to take it specifically for 189.
